I updated the parser to now extract both the numeric value **and** the bit-width suffix (e.g., `U8`, `U16`), then validate that the value fits within the range `[0, 2^bits - 1]`:

```typescript
const match = tuffSourceCode.match(/^(\d+)U(\d+)/);
// ...
const maxValue = (1 << bits) - 1;
if (value > maxValue) {
  throw new Error(`Value exceeds maximum for U${bits}`);
}
```

Now `executeTuff("256U8")` throws with the unique message `"Value exceeds maximum for U8"` since a U8 can only hold values up to 255.
